  "created": "2025-10-13",
  "description": "RNA polymerase (RNAP) recycling is the process by which RNAP is released from terminated transcripts and reassembled with sigma factors for new rounds of transcription initiation. This process involves termination (Rho-dependent or intrinsic), core enzyme release, sigma factor exchange, and reinitiation at promoters. The recycling pathway is critical for efficient gene expression, with regulatory mechanisms controlling sigma factor competition and RNAP availability. The process demonstrates computational logic in managing the transcriptional machinery pool and coordinating global gene expression programs.",
  "id": "ecoli_rna_polymerase_recycling",
