    "and": 8,
    "not": 3,
    "or": 0
  },
  "mermaid": "graph TD\n    %% Transcription Elongation Context\n    A[Active Transcription Elongation] --> B[RNAP Approaching Gene End]\n    B --> C[/Termination Signal<br/>Type?/]\n    \n    %% Intrinsic Termination Pathway\n    C -->|Intrinsic| D[Hairpin Formation in RNA]\n    D --> E[U-Rich Sequence]\n    E --> F[RNA-DNA Hybrid Destabilization]\n    F --> G[Transcript Release]\n    G --> H[Core RNAP Release]\n    \n    %% Rho-Dependent Termination Pathway\n    C -->|Rho-Dependent| I[Rho Binding to rut Site]\n    I --> J[Rho Hexamer Assembly]\n    J --> K[ATP-Dependent Translocation]\n    K --> L[Rho Catches RNAP]\n    L --> M[RNA-DNA Unwinding]\n    M --> N[Transcript Release]\n    N --> O[Core RNAP Release]\n    \n    %% Core Enzyme State\n    H --> P[Free Core Enzyme]\n    O --> P\n    P --> Q[Core RNAP in Cytoplasm]\n    \n    %% Sigma Factor Availability\n    R[Sigma Factor Pool] --> S{Which Sigma<br/>Factor?}\n    S -->|\u03c370| T[Sigma-70 Available]\n    S -->|\u03c338| U[Sigma-38 Available]\n    S -->|\u03c332| V[Sigma-32 Available]\n    S -->|Other| W[Alternative Sigma]\n    \n    %% Anti-Sigma Regulation\n    T --> X{Anti-Sigma<br/>Present?}\n    X -->|No| Y[Free Sigma-70]\n    X -->|Yes| Z[Sigma Sequestered]\n    \n    %% Holoenzyme Formation\n    Q --> AA{Core RNAP<br/>Available?}\n    Y --> AA\n    \n    AA --> ANDGATE1{Core Available AND<br/>Sigma Available?}\n    ANDGATE1 -->|Yes| AB[Core-Sigma Association]\n    ANDGATE1 -->|No| AC[Wait State]\n    \n    AB --> AD[RNAP Holoenzyme Formation]\n    AD --> AE[Holoenzyme in Cytoplasm]\n    \n    %% Promoter Recognition\n    AF[Promoter DNA] --> AG{Promoter<br/>Accessible?}\n    AG -->|Yes| AH[Open Promoter]\n    AG -->|No| AI[\\Blocked Promoter/]\n    \n    AE --> AJ{Holoenzyme Finds<br/>Promoter?}\n    AH --> AJ\n    \n    AJ -->|Yes| AK[Promoter Recognition]\n    AK --> AL[Closed Complex Formation]\n    AL --> AM[DNA Melting]\n    AM --> AN[Open Complex Formation]\n    \n    %% Transcription Initiation\n    AN --> AO{NTPs and<br/>Factors Ready?}\n    AO --> ANDGATE2{Open Complex AND<br/>NTPs Available?}\n    \n    ANDGATE2 -->|Yes| AP[Abortive Initiation Cycles]\n    AP --> AQ[Promoter Clearance]\n    AQ --> AR[Sigma Release]\n    AR --> AS[Elongation Complex]\n    \n    %% Recycling Complete\n    AS --> AT[New Transcript Synthesis]\n    AR --> AU[Sigma Returns to Pool]\n    AU --> R\n    \n    %% Failed Paths\n    Z --> AV[Reduced Transcription]\n    AC --> AW[Delayed Reinitiation]\n    AI --> AX[/No Transcription/]\n    \n    %% Styling - GLMP Color Scheme\n    %% Red: Triggers & Inputs\n    \n    %% Yellow: Structures & Objects\n    \n    %% Green: Processing & Operations\n    \n    %% Blue: Intermediates & States\n    \n    %% Orange: OR Logic Gates\n    \n    %% Lavender: AND Logic Gates\n    \n    %% Violet: Products & Outputs\n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n\n    %% Semantic Color Styling\n    style A fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style B fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style C fill:#e74c3c,color:#fff\n    style D fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style E fill:#51cf66,color:#fff\n    style F fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style G fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style H fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style I fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style J fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style K fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style L fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style M fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style N fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style O fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style P fill:#ffa726,color:#fff\n    style Q fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style S fill:#7950f2,color:#fff\n    style R fill:#ffa726,color:#fff\n    style T fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style U fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style V fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style W fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style X fill:#7950f2,color:#fff\n    style Y fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style Z fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AA fill:#7950f2,color:#fff\n    style ANDGATE1 fill:#7950f2,color:#fff\n    style AB fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AC fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AD fill:#ffa726,color:#fff\n    style AE fill:#ffa726,color:#fff\n    style AG fill:#7950f2,color:#fff\n    style AF fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AH fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AI fill:#e74c3c,color:#fff\n    style AJ fill:#7950f2,color:#fff\n    style AK fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AL fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AM fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AN fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AO fill:#7950f2,color:#fff\n    style ANDGATE2 fill:#7950f2,color:#fff\n    style AP fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AQ fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AR fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AS fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AT fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style AU fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AV fill:#42a5f5,color:#fff\n    style AW fill:#b3e5fc,color:#000\n    style AX fill:#e74c3c,color:#fff",
  "name": "RNA Polymerase Recycling and Reinitiation",
  "notGates": 3,
  "notes": "This flowchart shows the complete RNAP recycling pathway with 48 nodes, demonstrating both intrinsic and Rho-dependent termination pathways converging to core enzyme release. Contains 7 OR logic gates (termination type, sigma factor selection, promoter accessibility, holoenzyme-promoter encounter, NTP availability, anti-sigma regulation, core/sigma availability) and 2 AND logic gates (holoenzyme formation requires core AND sigma; reinitiation requires open complex AND NTPs). The model includes sigma factor competition (\u03c370, \u03c338, \u03c332, alternatives), anti-sigma factor regulation, and the complete cycle from termination through reinitiation. This represents the computational logic of managing the transcriptional machinery pool in response to cellular needs.",
  "organism": "E. coli",
  "relatedProcesses": [
    "ecoli_transcription_regulation",
    "ecoli_stringent_response"
  ],
  "scientificAccuracy": "This flowchart is based on extensive biochemical and structural studies of E. coli transcription termination, sigma factor dynamics, and RNAP recycling. The pathway represents current understanding of how RNAP transitions from elongation to termination to reinitiation, including the roles of termination factors (Rho, NusA), sigma factor exchange, and anti-sigma factors. All molecular components and regulatory mechanisms have been validated against primary research sources. Logic gates represent actual decision points in RNAP fate determination.",
